                            <comment id="17088430" author="mauromol" created="Tue, 21 Apr 2020 08:34:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please note closure argument types are not inferred even if I try to help the static type checker in this way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
Test64J j = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Test64J(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;hello&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, { foo, bar -&amp;gt;
			println(bar.size())
		} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; BiConsumer&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;, ? &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt; List&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case, the Groovy Eclipse Plugin (by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emilles&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emilles&quot;&gt;emilles&lt;/a&gt;) infers &lt;tt&gt;foo&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;bar&lt;/tt&gt; types correctly, but then still fails on the &lt;tt&gt;println&lt;/tt&gt; call probably because the Groovy static type checker fails.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
